<p><br class=3D"atl-forced-newline"> <br class=3D"atl-forced-newline"> <str=
ong><span style=3D"text-decoration: underline;">Summary</span></strong>: </=
p>=20
<ol>=20
<li>Highest precedence would be for the value where all attributes are cons=
idered - 4 in the above case i.e. MinAttributeValue, MaxAttributeValue, Con=
struction Group, Occupancy Group.</li>=20
<li>Second precedence would be for 3 attributes i.e. MinAttributeValue, Max=
AttributeValue and either Occupancy Group or Construction Group.</li>=20
<li>If no other attribute matches then by default only MinAttributeValue, M=
axAttributeValue would be considered and respective damage ratio for the lo=
cation Id would be taken.</li>=20
<li>In the case of more than two columns are added then precedence of the c=
olumns goes on decreasing from left to right i.e. column next to MinAttribu=
teValue would be the highest precedent column and the last column before DR=
 would be the least precedent column.</li>=20
</ol>=20
<p><br class=3D"atl-forced-newline"> <span style=3D"text-decoration: underl=
ine;">Points to remember while using this functionality:</span> <br class=
=3D"atl-forced-newline"></p>=20
<ol>=20
<li>Fixed columns :</li>=20
</ol>=20
<ul>=20
<li>In case of shape Analysis job 1<sup>st</sup> and 2<sup>nd</sup> column =
in the excel sheet should always be "MinAttributeValue" and "MaxAttributeVa=
lue" whereas the last column should be DR (damage ratio)</li>=20
<li>In case of custom shape Analysis 1<sup>st</sup> column in the excel she=
et should always be "ShapeName" whereas the last column should be DR (damag=
e ratio)</li>=20
<li>In case of Ring Analysis 1<sup>st</sup> column in the excel sheet shoul=
d always be "Radius" whereas the last column should be DR (damage ratio)</l=
i>=20
</ul>=20
<p><br class=3D"atl-forced-newline"></p>=20
<ol>=20
<li>Following naming convention should be followed while inserting columns<=
/li>=20
</ol>=20
<ul>=20
<li>Building Class : BLDGCLASS</li>=20
<li>Construction Group : CONSTRUCTION_GROUP</li>=20
<li>Occupancy Type : OCCTYPE</li>=20
<li>Occupancy Group <span style=3D"color: rgb(163,21,21);">:</span> OCC_MAJ=
OROCCUPANCYGROUP</li>=20
<li>Building Scheme : BLDGSCHEME</li>=20
<li>Occupancy Scheme : OCCSCHEME</li>=20
<li>Number Of Stories : NUMSTORIES</li>=20
<li>Year Built : YEARBUILT</li>=20
<li>Year Built Range: YEARBUILTRANGE</li>=20
<li>Number Of Stories Range : NUMSTORIESRANGE</li>=20
</ul>=20
<p><br class=3D"atl-forced-newline"></p>=20
<ol>=20
<li>While creating ranges make sure that the lowest value in the range is e=
ither redundant or lower than the possible lowest value in the data. For ex=
ample, if different locations have yearbuilt from 1942 to 2016 then minimum=
 range in the excel should be 1940 or 41 but not 1942.</li>=20
</ol>=20
<p><br class=3D"atl-forced-newline"></p>=20
<ol>=20
<li>Always provide default case Damage ratio. If default value is not provi=
ded then in those scenarios where no match is found in the .csv, damage rat=
io 0 would be assigned.</li>=20
</ol>=20
<p>To illustrate consider the following file data:</p>=20
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>=20
<tr>=20
